manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Color Assortment From the bright and stylish design to the accent pops of color, you will never have to worry about keeping track of these eye-catchers! Black Plum Teal Samsonite Ascella X Flight inspired engineering pushes materials and geometric structures to perform beyond their limits. Lightweight construction and performance materials merge. Simple but considered design with upgrades to wheels, hardware, branding, touchpoints and interior organization, pushing this next generation of product to the next level. 20” Spinner* 20 x 14.5 x 8, 7.1 lbs. 25” Spinner 24.5 x 17.75 x 9.5, 7.9 lbs. 29” Spinner 29 x 20.25 x 11, 9.5 lbs.

Functional and Thoughtful Design 360 Dual Spinner Wheels This lightweight line offers heavyweight protection riding on effortless 360 degree Spinner Wheels. All you need to do is push your case along and the wheels do the rest. Whether you are checking into to the flight or your hotel, it is super-easy with spinner wheels Push-Button Handle Deluxe cushioning and soft rubber seals on our, wider pull handle combine to provide an exceptionally comfortable grip. Integrated, multi-stage aluminum pull handle for extra lightness. Retracting top and side carry-handles remain protected when checking baggage. Expansion Design includes expansion for added packing capacity when needed. Consumer preferred expansion on only 24" and 28".

About Samsonite Samsonite’s not just in the business of making luggage, we’re in the business of building confidence. Confidence that when you step off the curb, your luggage wheel isn't going to pop off. Confidence that if you put your laptop in the bag in one piece, that’s the way it will come out. Samsonite has set an industry precedence by perfecting and innovating luggage, casual bags, backpacks, travel accessories, and now electronics carriers and laptop bags. Over one hundred years of reliability, durability, style and innovative functionality have made Samsonite’s iconic products, and brand, the global leader they are today. If you are going to head out the door, do it with peace of mind. Because, life has a way of coming at you fast. Be ready for anywhere.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect replacement for my old one
reviews.reviewText: This was purchased to replace the same make and model bag that i had used for years, but the pull out handle failed on it.This is, IMHO, the perfect carry on bag. I find that if I can get the zippers to close, no matter how much I have stuffed in the bag, that it will fit in the overhead bin of a 737 (the plane I fly most in).The wheels don't look very tough, but we will see. They don't look as beefy as those that were on my old bag; time will tell.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Bought this suitcase to replace an older Samsonite and like how much lighter it is. I use it for personal and business use. Easily pack clothes for a week with varying temperatures. The interior pockets work nicely for my needs. Able to organize more than I could before. Rolls like a dream. Handle is sturdy. Wheels became the issue with my old one after approx. 15 years.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I took this on a work trip last week, it worked great, I packed a ton into it and didn’t even need to expand, although that is probably my packing ability more than the suitcase… it rolls very nicely BUT I will say once I attached my backpack on top it was harder to roll without tipping over, especially on carpeted areas of the airport. It’s still easy to roll on two wheels though until you get back to tile.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars As spacious as it gets for a carry-on size
reviews.reviewText: I've looked around at the few most popular luggage brands - this Ascella X model has the largest interior dimensions while still being good for US carry on size. This is the 4th one we've bought - used the other 3 for about 9 months. All have easy maneuverability and other simple and sturdy construction.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not Samsonite quality - Nightmare warranty
reviews.reviewText: So I got this a year ago and bought it because I had other Samsonite luggage that I’ve had for a good 10 years. This set doesn't live up yo Samsonite quality and stuck with it at this point.First one of the zipper pulls just came right off as if I shaved it off when I pulled it. Then another pulled tab came off and finally a third one came off.I started the warranty process amd sent pictures. They said I had to deliver the luggage to one of their dealers, which is about 40 minutes away from me, amd then they would charge me $20 to ship it yo NY. After contacting them I was told I could pay to ship it to them directly. If they found it didn’t fall under the warranty I would have to pay to have it shipped back in for the repair.I sent them pictures and yet they still couldn’t tell me if it fell under warranty the idea of having to pay at least $40 to ship it back-and-forth for them to tell me if it under warranty was insane I’ll be better off buying new suitcases.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My new favorite piece of luggage! Perfect size and the color is great. Wheels roll 360 very smoothly. Handle is strong enough and is easy to retract. If you've ever had luggage where the handle gets stuck and won't pull up and down smoothly - you will appreciate this one!

Muy buenas maletas. Ya usamos las dos para un viaje largo en avion y no tuvimos ningún problema con ellas. Funcionan bien, la pequeña pudimos meterla al avion sin problema, de buen tamaño, se expanden. Muy complacidos con la compra.

reviews.reviewTitle: The quality of this suitcase is not up to scratch.
reviews.reviewText: On our first trip to Rome, the telescopic handle simply didn't work, and if you use the side handle to carry it, the body of the case gets all twisted up.To sum upThe quality of the telescopic handle is not robust enough for the size of the suitcase.With a weight of 48lbs / 21kilo, if you use the side handle for transport, the body of the suitcase becomes all twisted.We've always been satisfied with Samsonite products, so if you travel a lot during the year, I wouldn't recommend this model.
